<body>
    <h1>Text Cheat Sheet</h1>
    <h2>Size and Typeface of Text</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Serif</th>
      <th>San-Serif</th>
      <th>Monospace</th>
    </tr>  
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <span class="code">Serif fonts have extra details on
the ends of the main strokes of
the letters. These details are
known as serifs.</span>
        </td>
        <td>
          <span class="code1">Sans-serif fonts have straight
ends to letters, and therefore
have a much cleaner design.
        </span>
          </td>
          <td>
            <span class="code2">Every letter in a monospace (or
fixed-width) font is the same
width. (Non-monospace fonts
have different widths.)
          </span>
            </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table> 
</body>
